n the mind is empty, the spirit settles; when the spirit settles, qi naturally returns. Thus, to fill the belly, one must first empty the mind. Mind and breath depending on each other, placing everything externally—this is how the mind is emptied.” He further cited Master Sanfeng’s *A Sprig of Flowers*:
“I am a touchstone, revealing high and low at once;
I am an iron steamed bun, hard to bite into;
I am a sea of purity, unstained by a speck of dust;
I am a luminous pearl, suspended in the void.”
